      "name": "Ssumzili",
      "sections": [
        {
          "image": {
            "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png",
            "name": "Additional Lore",
            "type": "image"
          },
          "name": "Hunting Patterns of Ssumzilis",
          "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
          "sidebar_type": "additional_lore",
          "sources": [
            {
              "link": {
                "alt": "Pathfinder #171: Hurricane's Howl pg. 85",
                "aonid": 101,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Pathfinder #171: Hurricane's Howl pg. 85",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Pathfinder #171: Hurricane's Howl",
              "page": 85,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "subtype": "sidebar",
          "text": "Being ambush hunters, ssumzilis tend to avoid hunting without the cover of rainfall whenever possible. A ssumzili encountered hunting on a sunny day is doing so out of desperation and is likely to be unpredictable and erratic as a result.",
          "type": "section"
        }
      ],
      "sources": [
        {
          "link": {
            "alt": "Pathfinder #171: Hurricane's Howl pg. 85",
            "aonid": 101,
            "game-obj": "Sources",
            "name": "Pathfinder #171: Hurricane's Howl pg. 85",
            "type": "link"
          },
          "name": "Pathfinder #171: Hurricane's Howl",
          "page": 85,
          "type": "source"
        }
      ],
      "text": "Ssumzilis are lanky, murderous fey who delight in the thrill of the hunt. They are particularly skilled/adept at stalking their prey in the rain and most commonly reside in rainforests and coastal regions, where frequent rain provides ample opportunity to hunt. Camouflaged by their cloud-gray skin, ssumzilis often compete in tests of stealth when hunting in groups, taking particular delight in approaching their quarry as closely as possible without being observed.",
      "type": "section"
    }
  ],
  "sources": [
